{"build_type":"library","description":"Advance function for the ordered child fiber kind (category 7). The child carries its launch index in per-fiber slot 6 and its input in slot 1. It computes its result (the shared worker body, doubling the input), then writes that result and a filled flag into its parent's ordered reorder buffer at offsets keyed by its launch index (results at 6+index, filled at 3+index; the parent's buffer pointer is read via the awaiter slot). It then calls the standard completion routing, which re-readies the parent. Writing by launch index is what lets the parent deliver in launch order regardless of completion order; the wake reuses the built routing, no eventfd, no clone.","module_name":"advance-ordered-child-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler","package_name":"advance-ordered-child-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler","function_definitions":{"advance-ordered-child-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"s","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"t","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"six","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":6},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"seven","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":7},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_na